Job Responsibility:
Monitor and maintain building systems, including HVAC, electrical, plumbing, fire protection, and security systems.
Plan and oversee preventive and corrective maintenance activities.
Troubleshoot and resolve facility-related issues to minimize downtime.
Coordinate with vendors, contractors, and service providers for repair and improvement works.
Ensure compliance with health, safety, and environmental regulations.
Support space planning and workplace optimization projects.
Manage facility assets, maintenance records, and documentation.
Assist with budgeting and cost control for facilities operations.
Conduct routine inspections to identify potential hazards or inefficiencies.
Respond to emergency facility situations as needed.
Other requirements at the customer's site
Job Requirement:
1. Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical, Electrical, or Facilities Engineering or a related field;
2. Able to adapt to short-term overtime work (pre-construction phase, later normal working hours);
3. Have more than one year working experience in facilities management or building maintenance;
4. Familiar in using Building Management Systems (BMS) or Computerized Maintenance Management Systems (CMMS);
5. Strong knowledge of building systems, equipment, and maintenance procedures;
6. Correct working attitude, strong learning ability, good operation and maintenance habits, strong execution ability and sense of responsibility, good communication ability, service awareness, able to withstand pressure;
7. Intuitive understanding of IDC infrastructure and power environment (air conditioning, power, temperature, humidity, etc.)

Responsibility:
Serve as a Level 1 (L1) Technical Support Engineer, providing timely resolution to customer issues including daily inquiries, troubleshooting, performance tuning, and system anomalies.
Log and track critical customer requests and product bugs; collaborate with backend engineering, product, and operations teams to drive resolutions and product improvements.
Use tools (e.g., ARMS, SLS, Cloud Monitor) to proactively identify risks in customers’ production systems and offer mitigation guidance.
Author clear technical documentation, incident post-mortems, and knowledge base articles to improve team efficiency and customer self-service.
Participate in 7×24 on-call or shift rotations to ensure timely support for customers in global regions.
Continuously learn emerging cloud technologies (e.g., containers, serverless, AI/ML) to enhance technical depth and deliver better architectural advice.
Requirement:
Bachelor’s degree or higher in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
3–5 years of hands-on experience in cloud computing, IT operations, technical support, or solutions delivery; 3
Demonstrated ability to independently troubleshoot and resolve complex technical issues;
Practical experience helping customers design, deploy, or optimize architectures on public cloud platforms (e.g., Alibaba Cloud, AWS, Azure, GCP);
Familiarity with enterprise IT systems and the ability to tailor cloud solutions for vertical industries (e.g., e-commerce, finance, gaming, media).
Solid understanding of Linux/Windows OS, networking fundamentals, and TCP/IP;
Hands-on experience with at least one database (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis, SQL Server)—including deployment, management, and tuning;
Deep expertise in at least one domain: systems, networking, databases, containers (Docker/K8s), cloud security, storage, big data, middleware, or SRE;
Strong customer orientation—able to communicate technical details clearly and empathetically;
Self-driven with analytical thinking and perseverance in solving tough problems;
Good collaboration skills and ability to produce high-quality technical documentation.
Chinese and English can be used as working languages at the same time.
